ty Row Remake Scares its own Star\"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090405001624/http://scifiwire.com/2009/04/sorority-row-remake-scare.php |date=2009-04-05 }}, SciFi Wire, April 3, 2009</ref>}}\n{{Alum|name=[[Anton Peterlin (soccer)|Anton Peterlin]]|year=2005|nota=Soccer player|ref=<ref>[http://www.cifsf.org/Sports/SoccerBoysAll-City2004-05.pdf Boys Soccer All-City 2004\u20132005] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091211102043/http://www.cifsf.org/Sports/SoccerBoysAll-City2004-05.pdf |date=2009-12-11 }}, CIF San Francisco Section: Academic Athletic Association. Accessed June 12, 2013.</ref><ref>CIF-SF: San Francisco Sports Information. [http://www.cifsf.org/Sports/SoccerBoysAll-City2003-04.pdf Boys Soccer All-City 2003\u20132004] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20091211102038/http://www.cifsf.org/Sports/SoccerBoysAll-City2003-04.pdf |date=2009-12-11 }}, CIF San Francisco Section: Academic Athletic Association. Accessed June 12, 2013.</ref>}}\n{{Alum|name=[[Rita Volk]]|year=2008|nota= (Born Margarita Volkovinskaya) Model and Actress. Star of [[Faking It (2014 TV series)]] |ref=<ref>[http://www.mtv.com/shows/faking_it/cast_member.jhtml?personalityId=16374 MTV Biography]</ref> }}\n{{Alum|name=[[Adrian Lamo]]|nota=Computer hacker, key figure in [[WikiLeaks]] case, and journalist who attended Lowell along with two other high schools.|ref=<ref>Pilkington, Ed [https://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/jan/03/adrian-lamo-bradley-manning-q-and-a\"Adrian Lamo on Bradley Manning: 'I knew my actions might cost him his life'\"] \"[[The Guardian]]\", January 03, 2013. Accessed September 02, 2016. \"More than two years after (WikiLeaks source) [[Chelsea Manning]]'s arrest, the man who gave him up talks to Ed Pilkington about how he made the decision.\"</ref><ref>Kirby, Carrie. [http://www.sfgate.com/business/article/Alleged-hacker-grounded-at-home-Accused-of-2587141.php#page-2 \"Alleged hacker grounded at home / Accused of breaking into N.Y.